      • test_solutionWithOneMockIV

        public void test_solutionWithOneMockIV()
        Unit test with one mock IV.

        Note: TermId.mockIV(VTE) is used to generate "mock" IVs by operators which produce values (such as SUBSTR()) that are not in the database. The termId for all "mock" IV is 0L. While TermId.equals(Object) takes the IVCache association into account, the association is not yet available when we are de-serializing an encoded solution and is not part of the key when the key is constructed using IVUtility.encode(IKeyBuilder, IV). In each case this can lead to incorrectly resolving two "mock" IVs to the same value in an internal case.

        See Also:
        Optimize serialization for query messages on cluster
